        "3": {
          "id": "3",
          "name": "script.js",
          "language": "js",
          "contents": "// Get a reference to the song display container\nconst songDisplay = document.querySelector('.song-display');\n// Get a reference to the song count display element\nconst songCountSpan = document.querySelector('.song-count');\n\n// Function to create an HTML song card using arrow notation\nconst createSongCard = (song) => {\n  const songCard = document.createElement('div');\n  songCard.classList.add('song-card'); // Add the song-card class for styling\n\n  // Set the inner HTML of the card using template literals\n  songCard.innerHTML = `\n    <p class=\"song-title\">${song.title}</p>\n    <p class=\"artist-name\">${song.artist}</p>\n    <p class=\"genre-mood\">${song.genre} | ${song.mood}</p>\n  `;\n\n  return songCard;\n};\n\n// Function to display all songs using arrow notation\nconst displaySongs = (songsToDisplay) => {\n  // Clear any existing song cards\n  songDisplay.innerHTML = '';\n\n  // Loop through the array of songs and add them to the display\n  songsToDisplay.forEach(song => {\n    const card = createSongCard(song);\n    songDisplay.appendChild(card);\n  });\n\n  // Update the song count display\n  songCountSpan.textContent = `${songsToDisplay.length} songs`;\n};\n\n// Function to filter songs by artist using arrow notation\nconst filterSongsByArtist = (songs, artistName) => {\n  if (artistName === \"\" || artistName === \"All Artists\") {\n    return songs; // If \"All Artists\" is selected, return all songs\n  } else {\n    // Use the .filter() method to create a new array with only matching songs\n    return songs.filter(song => song.artist === artistName);\n  }\n};\n\n// Get references to the filter dropdowns\nconst artistFilter = document.getElementById('artist-filter');\n// TODO: Get references for genre-filter and mood-filter as well\n\n// Function to handle filtering and displaying songs using arrow notation\nconst applyFilters = () => {\n  const selectedArtist = artistFilter.value; // Get the currently selected artist from the dropdown\n\n  // Apply the artist filter\n  const filteredByArtist = filterSongsByArtist(allSongs, selectedArtist);\n\n  // TODO: Apply genre and mood filters here\n\n  // Display the filtered songs and update the count\n  displaySongs(filteredByArtist);\n};\n\n// Add event listener to the artist filter dropdown\nartistFilter.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);\n\n// Initial display of all songs when the page loads\ndisplaySongs(allSongs);\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": false
        },
        "4": {
          "id": "4",
          "name": "music_dashboard_plan.md",
          "language": "md",
          "contents": "# Music Habits Dashboard\n\nMy idea is to create an interactive music dashboard. I want to build a tool that lets people filter songs by things like genre and mood. I think it would be cool to see how many songs match your filters. This is useful because it's like a simplified version of a real music app.\n\n## My Plan\n\n- Use a dataset of songs that includes things like artist, title, genre, and maybe a \"mood\" tag\n- Create a dashboard with dropdowns for the filters\n- Use loops to go through the song list and show only the ones that match the filters\n- Use a loop to count how many songs are left after the filters are applied\n\n## My Dataset\n\nMy data is an array of objects, and each object is a song. This is the raw data I will use to build my dashboard.\n\n- music_data.js\n\n## Fairness\n\nI think my filters could be unfair if a user is looking for a specific type of music that my dashboard doesn't have. For example, if I only include popular songs, it might make other genres seem less important. My default view that shows all songs is important because it doesn't hide anything right away.\n\n## Artifact Checklist\n\n- [x] music_dashboard_plan.md\n- [x] music_data.js\n- [x] wireframe sketches\n- [x] index.html\n- [x] style.css\n- [x] script.js\n- [ ] reflection on fairness\n- [ ] AI collaboration log\n\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": false
        },
        "5": {
          "id": "5",
          "name": "music_data.js",
          "language": "js",
          "contents": "const allSongs = [\n  {\n    title: \"Blitzkrieg Bop\",\n    artist: \"Ramones\",\n    genre: \"Punk\",\n    mood: \"Energetic\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Cherry Bomb\",\n    artist: \"The Runaways\",\n    genre: \"Punk\",\n    mood: \"Rebellious\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Lo-fi Study Beats\",\n    artist: \"Lo-fi Fruits Music\",\n    genre: \"Lo-fi\",\n    mood: \"Relaxing\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Coffee Shop Jazz\",\n    artist: \"Chillhop Music\",\n    genre: \"Lo-fi\",\n    mood: \"Calm\"\n  }\n];\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": false
        }
